Example: 
```sv
interface foo #();

  logic baz; 

  modport slave (
    input baz 
  );

  modport master (
    output baz 
  );

endinterface

module bar (
    foo.slave qux[3:0]
);

    logic [3:0] quz;

    always_comb
    begin
        for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++)
        begin
           quz[i] = qux[i].baz; 
        end
    end

endmodule
```

What 'verilator' command line do we use to run your example?
`verilator -sv -Wall --lint-only` . 

I'm running it via svlangserver lsp.

What 'verilator --version' are you using?  Did you try it with the git master version?
I've tried this on multiple versions. The issue is not present in 4.228, but appears to be present in 5+. I have tried it on v5.002 and the stable branch (v5.32).

What OS and distribution are you using?
Ubuntu 24.02

I have not tried to fix it, I just switched to verilator 4.228 which does not throw this error.

Relevant Older Issues:
https://github.com/verilator/verilator/issues/1418

